{"type":"message","id":"b958df7c","parentId":"6c573c06","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:29:07.063Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_elk6pu8w3i5r_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 032726\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine a concrete action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals and the \"NEXT ACTION: TIC Experiment\":\r\n- Need to implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe current pending actions include:\r\n- Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n- Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\r\n- Tune λ empirically (start: λ=0.7)\r\n- Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n- Measure compression ratio: original vs. summarized pulse\r\n\r\nAnd the Phase 1 Advancement: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - specifically the TIC Experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist in the logs directory and what the current state is. I should look at the most recent pulse log and understand the structure to implement the TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nLet me look at the logs directory to see what pulse logs exist and their format.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\nLooking at the current state - the TIC Experiment is the next priority action. I need to examine the existing pulse logs to understand their structure before implementing the Temporal Invariance Compression classifier.\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC Experiment requires analyzing existing pulse logs to classify invariant vs. variant content. I need to first examine the structure and content of the pulse log files before implementing the classifier.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nExamine the most recent pulse logs to understand their structure and content patterns, then create the initial TIC classifier implementation skeleton.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n## Hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n- **Goal**: Test if invariant/variant classification >70% and next-pulse prediction >60%\r\n- **Method**: Analyze pulse logs for recurring patterns vs unique content\r\n\r\n## Classification Criteria\r\n\r\n### Invariants (persistent across pulses)\r\n- File paths and directory structures\r\n- Core architecture decisions\r\n- Active/completed phases\r\n- Pending action items (stable across sessions)\r\n\r\n### Variants (session-specific)\r\n- Timestamps and dates\r\n- Specific numbers (counts, ratios)\r\n- Observations about current state\r\n- Newly added items\r\n\r\n## Log Analysis\r\n\r\n### Pulse log structure to extract:\r\n- Goals section (stable → invariant)\r\n- Pending actions (relatively stable → invariant)\r\n- Recent history (variant → session-specific)\r\n- Notes (mixed → need classification)\r\n\r\n## Success Metrics\r\n- [ ] >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] >60% next-pulse content prediction from invariants\r\n\r\n## Implementation Plan\r\n1. Parse last 20 pulse logs\r\n2. Extract goal/pending content\r\n3. Classify each line as invariant or variant\r\n4. Measure classification accuracy (manual validation sample)\r\n5. Predict next pulse goals from invariants\r\n6. Compare prediction to actual next pulse\r\n\r\n---\r\n*Created: 2026-03-24*\r\n*Status: IN PROGRESS*\r\nfile: research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 03:27:52\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774337347061}}
